name: Dziś do ciebie przyjść nie mogę
comments: Dziś do ciebie przyjść nie mogę ("I can't come to you today") or Kołysanka ("The Lullaby") is a World War II "partisan" song from occupied Poland. Both lyrics and music were written in 1943 by Stanisław Magierski (nom de guerre "Jacek II"), a pharmacist from Lublin and a member of the Resistance. The most widely known version of the song, however, differs significantly from Magierski's original version, as the song was passed around through word of mouth. The lyrics describe the longing of a partisan, who is unable to come and see his beloved, because he has to hide out in the forest.
